&lt;p&gt;The coroutine is suppose &lt;code&gt;return&lt;/code&gt; on &lt;code&gt;GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; marking end of generator.
If the coroutine &lt;code&gt;return&lt;/code&gt; then &lt;code&gt;RuntimeError: generator ignored GeneratorExit&lt;/code&gt; is raised.
On &lt;code&gt;return&lt;/code&gt; the coroutine has ended hence it will throw &lt;code&gt;StopIteration&lt;/code&gt; if &lt;code&gt;send&lt;/code&gt; is called.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The coroutine also has a method &lt;a href="https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#coroutine.throw"&gt;throw&lt;/a&gt; which can be used to throw exception.
This interface is used throw &lt;code&gt;Reset&lt;/code&gt; exception which reset the state to &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="python"></category></entry></feed>